        <did>
          <unittitle>Hladia Porter Stewart</unittitle>
        </did>
        <scopecontent>
          <p>The second portion of the collection is made up of the writings of Hladia Porter Stewart. Consisting of numerous unpublished and privately printed books of poetry, plays and stories, these writings all relate to India. During her years in India, she contributed articles to local English language newspapers and magazines. Hladia Stewart was also an artist and some of her written work is illustrated with black and white drawings and watercolors. One small folder contains contemporary information about her teaching experiences at a girls college in India during the 30's and 40's. Another small folder contains material about the violence she observed during the creation of the Pakistani nation in 1947.</p>
        </scopecontent>
